# Paraglide writes `*` here by default to mark this directory as
# generated. We intentionally override that — see /CLAUDE.md
# ("Why src/paraglide/ is committed") for the rationale.
#
# Tracked files in this directory stay tracked even if paraglide
# rewrites this file on a future build. If the compiler ADDS a new
# file (e.g. you added a new message key), force-track it with:
#
#     git add -f src/paraglide/messages/<new-key>.js
#
# A `pnpm run build` (or `astro build`) regenerates everything here.
